  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class AssetCatalogException
extends OMAGCheckedExceptionBase
    AssetCatalogException provides a checked exception for reporting errors found when using the Asset Catalog OMAS services. Typically these errors are either configuration or operational errors that can be fixed by an administrator or power AssetConsumerInterface. However, there may be the odd bug that surfaces here. The AssetCatalogErrorCode can be used with this exception to populate it with standard messages. The aim is to be able to uniquely identify the cause and remedy for the error.
